    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1912-01-13T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1912-01-13T00:00:00-05:00" n="1358"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1358">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 412.11/48.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                            <gloss type="to">American Ambassador</gloss>
                    </hi>.</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.—Paraphrase.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1912-01-13">
                            <hi rend="italic">January 13, 1912</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>You will make representations regarding Douglas and El Paso incidents as directed
                    in Department’s January 8. But in view of your report of the seeming attitude of
                    the Mexican Government, you may if you deem it advisable make them in more
                    urgent terms than the Department has indicated.</p>
                <p>The Department desires information regarding the attitude of each of the other
                    powers towards all classes of claims, not merely personal injury claims; also
                    the general attitude of the Commission toward all classes of claims.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Knox.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
